.TH "regs_within_kernel_stack" 9 "regs_within_kernel_stack" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regs_within_kernel_stack \- check the address in the stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" regs_within_kernel_stack
.BI "(struct pt_regs *regs "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "regs" 12
pt_regs which contains kernel stack pointer.
.IP "addr" 12
address which is checked.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBregs_within_kernel_stack\fP checks \fIaddr\fP is within the kernel stack page(s).
If \fIaddr\fP is within the kernel stack, it returns true. If not, returns false.
